68w, https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/weymouth-seabream.jpg 1400w" sizes="(max-width: 670px) 100vw, 670px" /></noscript></a><br />
<a href="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/horse-mackerel-mars-skelter.jpg"><img src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%27http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%27%20width='670'%20height='823'%20viewBox=%270%200%20670%20823%27%3E%3C/svg%3E" loading="lazy" data-lazy="1" style="background:linear-gradient(to right,#1f1f17 25%,#15100a 25% 50%,#11100e 50% 75%,#615d54 75%),linear-gradient(to right,#1e1b14 25%,#cdc8ab 25% 50%,#585449 50% 75%,#4b443c 75%),linear-gradient(to right,#b3afa4 25%,#524d30 25% 50%,#7b6f79 50% 75%,#131311 75%),linear-gradient(to right,#3e3b36 25%,#413d31 25% 50%,#181712 50% 75%,#867352 75%)" decoding="async" data-tf-src="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/horse-mackerel-mars-skelter-670x823.jpg" alt="Horse Mackerel on Mars Skelter" width="670" height="823" class="tf_svg_lazy alignnone size-large wp-image-20229" data-tf-srcset="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/horse-mackerel-mars-skelter-670x823.jpg 670w, https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/horse-mackerel-mars-skelter-244x300.jpg 244w, https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/horse-mackerel-mars-skelter-190x233.jpg 190w, https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/horse-mackerel-mars-skelter-768x943.jpg 768w, https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/horse-mackerel-mars-skelter.jpg 1140w" data-tf-sizes="(max-width: 670px) 100vw, 670px" /><noscript><img decoding="async" data-tf-not-load src="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/horse-mackerel-mars-skelter-670x823.jpg" alt="Horse Mackerel on Mars Skelter" width="670" height="823" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-20229" srcset="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/horse-mackerel-mars-skelter-670x823.jpg 670w, https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/horse-mackerel-mars-skelter-244x300.jpg 244w, https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/horse-mackerel-mars-skelter-190x233.jpg 190w, https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/horse-mackerel-mars-skelter-768x943.jpg 768w, https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/horse-mackerel-mars-skelter.jpg 1140w" sizes="(max-width: 670px) 100vw, 670px" /></noscript></a><br />
Amazing sport down in Weymouth this week. It seemed like everything was on, from tiny gobies to squid. </p>
<div class="more-link-wrap"><a class="more-link" href="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/2024/09/weymouth-september-bonanza/">More</a></div></div></div></div></article> <article id="post-20222" class="post tf_clearfix cat-5 cat-224 post-20222 type-post status-publish format-image has-post-thumbnail hentry category-image category-september tag-dorset tag-goby tag-hto tag-hto-knight-worms tag-leopard-spotted-goby tag-weymouth post_format-post-format-image has-post-title has-post-date has-post-category has-post-tag has-post-comment has-post-author "><div class="post-inner tf_clearfix"><span class="post-icon"></span><time datetime="2024-09-05" class="post-date entry-date updated">5th September, 2024</time><h2 class="post-title entry-title"><a href="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/2024/09/leopard-spotted-goby-on-unflavoured/">Leopard-spotted Goby on Unflavoured</a></h2><div class="post-content"> <div class="entry-content"> <p><a href="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/leopard-spotted-goby-lure.jpg"><img src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%27http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%27%20width='670'%20height='503'%20viewBox=%270%200%20670%20503%27%3E%3C/svg%3E" loading="lazy" data-lazy="1" style="background:linear-gradient(to right,#020305 25%,#403d34 25% 50%,#9c5730 50% 75%,#373938 75%),linear-gradient(to right,#454337 25%,#0e0e1a 25% 50%,#949bd2 50% 75%,#2026b8 75%),linear-gradient(to right,#5d5b4e 25%,#584f54 25% 50%,#867e8d 50% 75%,#feffff 75%),linear-gradient(to right,#6e6b62 25%,#74746a 25% 50%,#33354a 50% 75%,#b9b6a5 75%)" decoding="async" data-tf-src="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/leopard-spotted-goby-lure-670x503.jpg" alt="Leopard-spotted Goby on Lure" width="670" height="503" class="tf_svg_lazy alignnone size-large wp-image-20223" data-tf-srcset="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/leopard-spotted-goby-lure-670x503.jpg 670w, https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/leopard-spotted-goby-lure-300x225.jpg 300w, https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/leopard-spotted-goby-lure-190x143.jpg 190w, https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/leopard-spotted-goby-lure-768x576.jpg 768w, https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/leopard-spotted-goby-lure.jpg 1400w" data-tf-sizes="(max-width: 670px) 100vw, 670px" /><noscript><img decoding="async" data-tf-not-load src="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/leopard-spotted-goby-lure-670x503.jpg" alt="Leopard-spotted Goby on Lure" width="670" height="503" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-20223" srcset="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/leopard-spotted-goby-lure-670x503.jpg 670w, https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/leopard-spotted-goby-lure-300x225.jpg 300w, https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/leopard-spotted-goby-lure-190x143.jpg 190w, https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/leopard-spotted-goby-lure-768x576.jpg 768w, https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/leopard-spotted-goby-lure.jpg 1400w" sizes="(max-width: 670px) 100vw, 670px" /></noscript></a><br />
Ecstatic with this one! Leopard-spotted Goby on unflavoured soft plastic. </p>
<div class="more-link-wrap"><a class="more-link" href="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/2024/09/leopard-spotted-goby-on-unflavoured/">More</a></div></div></div></div></article> </div><link rel="prefetch" as="document" href="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/page/2/"/><div class="pagenav tf_clear tf_box tf_textr tf_clearfix "> <span class="number current">1</span> <a href="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/page/2/" class="number">2</a> <a href="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/page/3/" class="number">3</a> <a href="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/page/4/" class="number">4</a><a href="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/page/2/" class="number nextp">&rsaquo;</a><a href="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/page/89/" title="&raquo;" class="number lastp">&raquo;</a></div> </main></div></div><div id="footerwrap"><footer id="footer" class="pagewidth tf_clearfix" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/WPFooter"><div class="footer-widgets tf_clearfix"><div class=" first"><div id="text-3" class="widget widget_text"><h4 class="widgettitle">About Light Rock Fishing</h4><div class="textwidget"><p>Light Rock Fishing, or LRF as it&#8217;s more commonly known means different things to different people. Essentially it&#8217;s ultra light lure fishing &#8211; requiring skill and finesse. It&#8217;s the perfect way to hone your general lure fishing skills and continues all year round. No longer do you need to pack up your lure fishing tackle in winter, once traditional sport species like Bass disappear. For others, like me, LRF is the ideal fishing discipline to target new and interesting species, helping us to notch-up record levels of species each season. To all though, young and old, experienced or beginner, LRF means incredibly fun fishing. Get involved!</p>
</div></div></div></div><p class="back-top"><a href="#header">&uarr;</a></p><ul id="footer-nav" class="footer-nav"><li id="menu-item-768" class="menu-item-page-5 menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-768"><a href="https://light.rockfishing.co.uk/contact/">Contact Adam</a></li>
